04/07/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Paddy Ashdown, the top international officer in BiH, and BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic set up a commission Friday (2 July) to create a single police force for the country's two entities.
Former Belgian Prime Minister Wilfried Martens will serve as chairman.
The panel has until the end of the year to draft a plan.
In other news, 12 Bosnian Serbs have been sentenced to prison terms of up to 17 months for selling arms to Iraq in violation of the UN embargo.
They include six customs officials and six executives of the Orao Company in Republika Srpska (RS).
Meanwhile, RS Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic met with an IMF delegation Friday.
They discussed the new standby arrangement with the Fund covering the period October 2004 to December 2005.
(AFP - 03/07/04;
FENA - 02/07/04)
